## SECURITY RULES — non-negotiable, apply to every session

### Secrets
- Credentials load from environment variables only — never from config files, never hardcoded
- {{SECRETS_CONFIG_LOCATION}} is the only place secrets are read from environment
- Agents/modules read credentials via the secrets config object — never `os.environ`/`process.env` directly in business logic
- Any config file containing real values is in `.gitignore` — only a `.example` version is committed
- `.env` is in `.gitignore` — never committed under any circumstances

### Logs
- No credential values, API keys, tokens, or private key paths in any log output at any level
- Sensitive payloads (prompts to external APIs, user PII) logged at DEBUG only, never INFO or above

### Git
- Before every commit: confirm no `.env`, no real config file, no `*.pem`/`*.key` in staged files
- If a secret is ever accidentally committed: rotate the credential immediately, then remove from git history (`git filter-repo` or equivalent)
